# Install and configure SonarQube (Master machine)
    docker run -itd --name SonarQube-Server -p 9000:9000 sonarqube:lts-community

    now open browwser http://ip:9000
    initial user & password 
    admin
    admin

2. Generate token on sonarqube website
    Click on Administration
        configuration > webhooks > create 
            name: Jenkins
            url: ip:8080/sonarqube-webhook/
        
        security > users , create token 
            name: Jenkins then click on Generate then copy token for futher use


# Install Trivy (Jenkins Worker)
    wget https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy/releases/download/v0.18.3/trivy_0.18.3_Linux-64bit.deb
    sudo dpkg -i trivy_0.18.3_Linux-64bit.deb

# OWASP

1. Configure OWASP, move to Manage Jenkins --> Plugins --> Available plugins (Jenkins Worker)
    SonarQube Scanner
    Sonar Quality Gates
    OWASP Dependency-check
    Docker

2. After OWASP plugin is installed, Now move to Manage jenkins --> sysrem (Jenkins Worker)
    under "SonarQube servers"
        click on "Sonar Qube installations"
            name: 
            url: ip:9000
            token: add token in credentials then select here

3. Manage jenkins --> tools
    "SonarQube Scanner installations" click on "add sonarqube scanner" , then fill details
        name: sonar
        click on "install automatically"

4. Manage jenkins --> tools
    "Dependecy-check installations" then click on "Add dependency check"
        name: dc
        click on "install automatically"
            add installer select "github.com"
            